  <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Process_Description">Process Description</span></h2>
  <p>The chapter on Demand Management in the Service Strategy book (ITIL V3 2007 Edition) did not offer enough substance to justify a separate Demand Management process, so at IT Process Maps we have decided to treat Demand Management as part of Capacity Management. </p>
  <p>As the latest <i><b>ITIL 2011</b></i> guidance includes clarifications on the differences in scope between Demand Management and Capacity Management, a specific Demand Management process has been introduced as part of Service Strategy. The process overview of <a href="/images/itilssfour.jpg"  title="Demand-management-itil.jpg">ITIL Demand Management (.JPG)</a> shows the key information flows. </p>
  <p>The role Demand Manager has been introduced to perform the activities in the Demand Management process. </p>
  <p>&#160;</p>
  <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Sub-Processes">Sub-Processes</span></h2>
  <p>No sub-processes are specified for <a class="mw-selflink selflink">ITIL Demand Management</a>. </p>
  <p>&#160;</p>
  <h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Definitions">Definitions</span></h2>
